summary: TO2 retry delay configured via --to2-retry-delay flag
description: |
    Tests the --to2-retry-delay flag that adds a delay between TO2
    owner attempts:
    - Multiple unreachable owners cause TO2 failures with delays
    - Configured 3s delay applied between each TO2 attempt
    - Final owner succeeds after retries

test: ./test-retry-to2-delay-configured.sh

framework: shell

duration: 10m

require:
  - go-fdo-server
  - go-fdo-server-manufacturer
  - go-fdo-server-owner
  - go-fdo-server-rendezvous

tag:
  - fdo
  - e2e
  - protocol
  - retry
  - to2
  - rpm
  - server
